(219, '''Cancer made me want mashed potato''', 'The strange effects of cancer on appetite', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-31641689#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(220, '''Improve end-of-life care'' - MPs', 'Social care should be free to everyone at the end of life, says a report by MPs which also calls for better recording of what people want in their final days.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-31871482#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(221, 'VIDEO: Welcome to the designer asylum', 'Why one artist has built the asylum of his dreams, a space he calls "a safe place to go mad".', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-32035911#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(222, 'VIDEO: Miliband: Cameron ''failed'' the NHS', 'Labour leader Ed Miliband says the National Health Service needs to be ''''rescued'''' from the Conservatives, while David Cameron insists there are more people being treated.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-32165446#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(223, 'VIDEO: ''We must plan for future of NHS''', 'As the 2015 election campaign gathers pace, the BBC speaks to a manager in the National Health Service - Matthew Fitzpatrick from London.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-32154255#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(224, 'VIDEO: Why are we having less sex?', 'Sex as a recreational activity, is in decline, according to Sex By Numbers, a new book on sexual behaviour written by David Spiegelhalter.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-32172629#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(225, 'VIDEO: Could existing drugs offer MS hope?', 'Depression and heart-disease drugs are to be tested in a trial to find treatments for Multiple Sclerosis (MS) from existing medicines.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-32137178#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(226, 'VIDEO: Disability village ''under threat''', 'The village of Botton in North Yorkshire has been home to people with learning disabilities for 60 years, but there are claims that the community could be under threat.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-32127040#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(227, 'VIDEO: Nursing code of conduct launched', 'A new code of conduct has been launched by the body that oversees 670,000 nurses and midwives in the UK.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-32127896#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
(228, 'VIDEO: Vaccine to protect from meningitis B', 'An agreement has been reached to provide a meningitis B vaccine for all babies in the UK, the BBC''s Sarah Campbell reports.', 'http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-32104724#sa-ns_mchannel=rss&ns_source=PublicRSS20-sa', 12),
